    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-01-21T10:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-01-21T10:00:00-05:00" n="86"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d86">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">850d.00/375: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wallace</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-01-21T15:00:00+00:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 21, 1920—3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received January 22—3:43 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>205. My mail despatch 609 of December 3 [<hi rend="italic">5</hi>] last.<note
                        n="58" xml:id="d86fn58">Not printed.</note>
                </p>
                <p>The Foreign Office asks for an immediate reply concerning the views of the
                    American Government on the convention concerning Spitzbergen and in the event
                    that it is decided to take part therein to inform the Foreign Office of the name
                    of the American plenipotentiary at the earliest possible moment.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wallace</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
